This paper focuses on the evaluation of a generative model that creates images related to climate change-induced flooding. The paper proposes several automated and human-based methods for evaluation, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the importance of public interest and awareness, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research. Additionally, the paper involves the visualization of data, which is a common theme in graphics (cs.GR) research.
